eNCA's Dan Moyane spoke with reporter Govan Whittles in Soweto. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Army medics will be used to bolster Gauteng's COVID-19 fighting capability. It is hoped the force multipliers will help frontline workers deal with overburdened facilities. READ: COVID-19: Bed shortages in Gauteng The province is currently the epicentre of the outbreak. On Sunday, the country recorded 13,155 new infections, with 8,640 of these in Gauteng.